pared with\n'that of Miss Hinkle, and her presence\nhere will be a delight to the musical\npublic. She has many friends among\nprofessional musicians tn this com\nmunity and her line art is familiar to\nmost of us.\nI\nFRATERNAL ORDERS\nXtl. ZION LODGE Nth 10.\nF. A V M.\nMeets I ir-t and t hird I hur-day\nNights in Each Month.\nNext Meeting\u2014\nThursday night, January 20.\nBMKSXIIIF (HIPIER. NO.\nR. A. M.\nStated onvix ation-. I\u00ab*t I ur\u00abda\u00bb\nNight in rai<h Month.\nNext Meeting\nTuesday night. January 25.\nST. El MO tOMMWDERi NO. 13,\nKNIt.HTS TEMPI VR\nMeet- Second Fridar Night in Each\nMonth.\nNext Meet in<\u2014\nFriday nitfht, January 14.\n\u2014o\u2014.\nRI 1H llxrrE\u00df. XO. 91. E. s.\nMrrf*i Srsond and Fourth Ihur^dav\nIftenMMMWi tn Each Month at\nMaaMk Hall.\nNext Mrrtinc\u2014\nThursday night. January 13.\nI. O. O. F.\nMeets Etery Friday Night in Each\nMonth.\nNext Meeting-\nFriday night, January 14.\nCITY OFFICERS\nJ. Paul Ward. Mayor\nT. Albert. Recorder.\nChas. C. Houston. Marshal.\nG. E. Gathri.ht, Treasurer.\n1 M. vasev. City Attorney.\nM. S. Craig. City Health Officer.\nT. M. Scarlett. Sextcn\nUse h Then Decide\n\nWe Will Lend You\nI\nA Valet AutoMrop Haioi \u00bbnr H)\ntria I* vr\u00bbia then dr de t rrp pay\nf*\u00bbr it. if not. fWii\u2019n it\nNo Risk No Obligation\nAay inponmW. pMty <sn arrange m\no\u00abr Cutlery counter few thr. f r.a Trial,\nwhich mean, you naad not era depvao\nits value It you have a charge account,\nwrite to u. and w. will mad lb. tin\n'a\nCASEY DRUG CO.\nAGENTS.\nPhone 7\u00bb. Free Delivery.","height":"19776","width":"13860"}}
